The paper deals with approximation algorithms for two variations of the traveling salesman problem with time windows, which are optimization problems related to algorithms, optimization, and robotics. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of weighted graphs and approximation algorithms, which are topics related to machine learning and optimization, respectively, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Systems and Control) possible sub-categories as well.
